         </sect1info>
         <title>
            <emphasis role="HeadingNumber">11.2 </emphasis> Reflective Exercises</title>
         <orderedlist continuation="restarts" inheritnum="ignore">
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What are the primary principles and practice of <emphasis>Santeria</emphasis>?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is meant by <emphasis>simpatia</emphasis>, <emphasis>personalismo</emphasis>, and <emphasis>choteo</emphasis>? How are they displayed by Cubans?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Explain the extensive name format used by Cubans.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Name at least three health conditions common among Cubans.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Identify at least three folk beliefs about pregnancy common to Cubans.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What are some common amulets used by Cubans to teat ailments?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>A female Cuban new diabetic patient wants to use herbs to control her diabetes. Would you encourage her to try herbs rather than allopathic treatments? Why or why not?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is a <emphasis>botanica</emphasis>? Is there one in your community?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Identify ways in which to integrate religious practices and preferences into the patient’s health-care plan.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is the most important source of emotional and physical support for most Cubans?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is a <emphasis>quinceañera?</emphasis>
               </para>
            </listitem>
         </orderedlist>
      </sect1>
