         </sect1info>
         <title>
            <emphasis role="HeadingNumber">17.2 </emphasis> Reflective Exercises</title>
         <orderedlist continuation="restarts" inheritnum="ignore">
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>In what languages would you prepare educational brochures for general health education for Haitians?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What are the primary roles of traditional Haitian men and Women?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Explain the principles of <emphasis>fret</emphasis> and <emphasis>cho</emphasis>. How are these principles applied in dietary practices? In health conditions?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What are the primary health conditions common with Haitians?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Explaining breast-feeding practices common with Haitian mothers. Which practices are potentially dangerous and how would you address them with the mother?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Explain the tenets of <emphasis>voodism</emphasis>. How is <emphasis>voodism</emphasis> seen in health-care practices?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Distinguish natural versus supernatural illness among Haitians.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is <emphasis>oppression</emphasis>? What education would you include in a patient who has <emphasis>oppression?</emphasis>
               </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What infectious diseases would you look for in recent immigrants from Haiti?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What are traditional Haitian verbal and nonverbal communication practices?</para>
            </listitem>
         </orderedlist>
      </sect1>
