               <personname>
                  <firstname>Eric A.</firstname>
                  <surname>Fenkl</surname>
               </personname>
            </primaryauthor>
         </sect1info>
         <title>
            <emphasis role="HeadingNumber">20.2 </emphasis> Reflective Exercises</title>
         <orderedlist continuation="restarts" inheritnum="ignore">
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is the national language of Iranians? What other languages spoken by Iranians?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is <emphasis>zerangi</emphasis> and how is it displayed?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>How should traditional Iranian men and women be addressed?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Describe Iranian family hierarchy and decision-making practices.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>How are Iranian gays and lesbians seen in Iran? What ramifications might this have in the US?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What are the primary health conditions among Iranians?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Explain <emphasis>garm</emphasis> and <emphasis>sard</emphasis>? What might you do if you are unfamiliar with this category of foods?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>An Iranian patient is near death. How do you discuss this situation with the Iranian family?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>How would you vary meals and medication administration during Ramadan?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is <emphasis>narahati,</emphasis> what is its significance, and what are its symptoms?</para>
            </listitem>
         </orderedlist>
      </sect1>
