               <chapterid>ch0022</chapterid>
               <chaptertitle>22. People of Italian Heritage</chaptertitle>
               <authorgroup>
                  <author>
                     <personname>
                        <firstname>Eric A.</firstname>
                        <surname>Fenkl</surname>
                     </personname>
                  </author>
                  <author>
                     <personname>
                        <firstname>Larry D.</firstname>
                        <surname>Purnell</surname>
                     </personname>
                  </author>
               </authorgroup>
               <publisher>
                  <publishername>Springer International Publishing</publishername>
               </publisher>
               <pubdate>2024</pubdate>
            </risinfo>
            <primaryauthor>
               <personname>
                  <firstname>Eric A.</firstname>
                  <surname>Fenkl</surname>
               </personname>
            </primaryauthor>
         </sect1info>
         <title>
            <emphasis role="HeadingNumber">22.2 </emphasis> Reflective Exercises</title>
         <orderedlist continuation="restarts" inheritnum="ignore">
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Describe traditional Italian American gender roles. What are their implications for health-care decision-making?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>How do you determine cyanosis and jaundice in dark-skinned Italians?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What are common health conditions for Italian Americans?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What are the dangers associated with the ingestion of fava beans and the administration of sulfonamides, antimalarial agents, salicylates, and naphthaquinolones in Italian Americans?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Identify several foods used for health promotion. What illnesses will they help prevent?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Identify some common beliefs and customs about pregnancy? Are any of them harmful?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>In traditional terms, to what are illnesses attributed?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Many traditional Italians believe in <emphasis>Il mal occhio</emphasis>. What is this and what is done to protect oneself?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What are <emphasis>maghi</emphasis> and <emphasis>streghe</emphasis>? What are their functions?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Explain the basic rites of the Sacrament of the Sick. What is the purpose?</para>
            </listitem>
         </orderedlist>
      </sect1>
