         <title>
            <emphasis role="HeadingNumber">24.2 </emphasis> Reflective Exercises</title>
         <orderedlist continuation="restarts" inheritnum="ignore">
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Japanese use the term <emphasis>sensei</emphasis> when referring to older people. What does this term mean?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Distinguish between male and female communication styles.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What does “saving face” mean? How is “saving face” used when communicating with health-care providers?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>List and explain at least three genetic health conditions common among the Japanese.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is the word for Japanese traditional healers? When might one purchase Japanese herbs?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What terms are used to distinguish three generations of Japanese?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is the traditional religion of the Japanese? What are some of its principal tenets?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Explain the concepts of <emphasis>yin</emphasis> and <emphasis>yang</emphasis> when referred to in health care.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Explain <emphasis>morita</emphasis> and <emphasis>naikan</emphasis> therapies<emphasis>.</emphasis> For what conditions are they used?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is <emphasis>itami</emphasis> and how it is expressed?</para>
            </listitem>
         </orderedlist>
      </sect1>
