                  <firstname>Eric A.</firstname>
                  <surname>Fenkl</surname>
               </personname>
            </primaryauthor>
         </sect1info>
         <title>
            <emphasis role="HeadingNumber">25.2 </emphasis> Reflective Exercises</title>
         <orderedlist continuation="restarts" inheritnum="ignore">
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is meant by<emphasis>
                     <emphasis role="bold">halakhah</emphasis>
                  </emphasis> and what does it emphasize?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Name and describe at least three genetic conditions common among Jews.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is meant by<emphasis>
                     <emphasis role="bold">kashrut</emphasis>
                  </emphasis>? Distinguish between kosher and <emphasis>treyf.</emphasis>
               </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What are the tenets of the four broad branches of Judaism? What are the primary differences among them?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>When does Sabbath begin and end?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Under what conditions are observant Jews able to work?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What are some of the major principles that guide Judaic bioethics?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is meant by <emphasis>shiva</emphasis>? Describe its practices.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>An orthodox Jewish couple is expecting their first child. The expectant father wants to be in the delivery room with his wife. What preparations do you need to make for this to occur?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>The hospital where you work does not have a kosher kitchen. Where might you purchase kosher meals? Once you have a kosher meal, how do you handle the food?</para>
            </listitem>
         </orderedlist>
      </sect1>
