         </sect1info>
         <title>
            <emphasis role="HeadingNumber">26.2 </emphasis> Reflective Exercises</title>
         <orderedlist continuation="restarts" inheritnum="ignore">
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>For Koreans, a response of “yes” may not have the same connotation as it does in the European American culture. What does it mean in the Korean culture?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Explain the name format for Koreans and how you would address them.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>When family violence is suspected, how might you approach the topic?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is <emphasis>hyo</emphasis> and how is it displayed?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What needs to be included in an orientation program for Koreans to be successful in the workforce?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Name at least three common health conditions among Koreans.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is <emphasis>Tae-Kyo</emphasis> and what is its purpose?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is the term for traditional Korean medicine and what are its principles?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is <emphasis>Hwa-Byung</emphasis> and what are its causes and symptoms?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>How do more traditional Koreans see disability?</para>
            </listitem>
         </orderedlist>
      </sect1>
