         </sect1info>
         <title>
            <emphasis role="HeadingNumber">27.2 </emphasis> Reflective Exercises</title>
         <orderedlist continuation="restarts" inheritnum="ignore">
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Describe the extensive name format for Mexican women. How would you address her? What is her legal name?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Describe eye contact protocol among traditional Mexicans.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>How do you assess for jaundice and cyanosis among dark-skinned Mexicans?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>List three common health conditions of Mexican that have a lifestyle component.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Describe Mexican folk healers and describe their treatment modalities.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What are the deciding factors for treating Mexicans with extraordinary illnesses?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Describe the “hot” and “cold” theory of illnesses among Mexicans.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Describe the “hot” and “cold” theory of food among Mexicans. If you are unfamiliar with foods in each category, what are your resources for finding out more?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>Two herbs commonly used by Mexican Americans are <emphasis>azarcon</emphasis> and <emphasis>greta</emphasis>, which are used for colic and stomach conditions in children. What are the hazards of giving them to children?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem role="ListItem">
               <para>What is the folk illness <emphasis>ataque de nervios</emphasis>. What are its symptoms? How would you treat it?</para>
            </listitem>
         </orderedlist>
      </sect1>
